00:52:13,172 --> 00:52:16,630
Oh, I was so very near him.

511
00:52:16,717 --> 00:52:21,427
And in many tears for the assurance
of the pardon of me sins.

512
00:52:21,513 --> 00:52:25,631
And I was so ravaged
with his love towards me,

513
00:52:25,726 --> 00:52:30,140
I thought it far exceeding
the affection of the kindest husband.

514
00:52:32,441 --> 00:52:34,773
And since Samuel disappeared...

515
00:52:36,612 --> 00:52:40,855
I have such a sad weakness
of faith, I cannot shake it.

516
00:52:40,949 --> 00:52:44,487
I cannot see Christ's help as near.

517
00:52:44,578 --> 00:52:47,741
I pray and I pray, but I cannot.

518
00:52:50,250 --> 00:52:54,994
I fear I cannot ever feel
that same measure of love again.

519
00:53:01,178 --> 00:53:03,885
Thou shall have of it in heaven.

520
00:53:07,768 --> 00:53:10,601
I'll be in field.

521
00:53:10,688 --> 00:53:13,521
If you can spare a while, do.

522
00:53:13,607 --> 00:53:15,268
We'll leave at dawn.

523
00:53:15,359 --> 00:53:17,099
I promise thee that.

524
00:53:22,825 --> 00:53:23,780
Jonas, mercy, come hither!

525
00:53:23,784 --> 00:53:23,863
Jonas, mercy, come hither!

526
00:53:23,867 --> 00:53:25,323
Jonas, mercy, come hither!

527
00:53:26,578 --> 00:53:28,364
Speak not a word!

528
00:53:39,383 --> 00:53:41,374
Black Phillip is a merry, merry king

529
00:53:41,468 --> 00:53:44,197
- he rules the land with mirth...
- Thomasin: I cannot abide your songs.

530
00:53:44,221 --> 00:53:45,961
Please you, mercy.

531
00:53:46,056 --> 00:53:47,637
Black Phillip has
a mighty, mighty sting

532
00:53:47,725 --> 00:53:49,465
he'll knock thee to the earth

533
00:53:49,560 --> 00:53:51,767
sing bah, bah,
king Phillip, the black

534
00:53:51,854 --> 00:53:53,581
- sing bah, bah, bah, bah, bah
- Thomasin: Peace, thou thing!

535
00:53:53,605 --> 00:53:55,345
Mercy. Thomasin.

536
00:53:55,441 --> 00:53:57,352
Sing bah, bah, king Phillip, the black

537
00:53:57,443 --> 00:53:59,483
- he'll knock thee on thy back!
- Thomasina: Enough!

538
00:54:03,824 --> 00:54:05,155
Come.

539
00:54:09,246 --> 00:54:11,953
Get the broadaxe
and cut off her head.

540
00:54:12,040 --> 00:54:15,203
Get the narrow axe
and cut off her head.

541
00:54:15,294 --> 00:54:17,751
Get the broadaxe
and cut off her head.

542
00:54:17,838 --> 00:54:20,124
Get the narrow axe
and cut off her head.

543
00:54:22,885 --> 00:54:24,546
She's upon me!

544
00:54:24,636 --> 00:54:26,092
She kneels!

545
00:54:26,180 --> 00:54:27,716
My bowels!

546
00:54:27,806 --> 00:54:30,047
My stomach!

547
00:54:30,142 --> 00:54:31,507
She pinches!

548
00:54:34,688 --> 00:54:38,601
Sin! Sin! Sin!

549
00:54:38,692 --> 00:54:41,149
Thomasin, take the children outside.

550
00:54:41,278 --> 00:54:43,940
What does this to thee?
What does this?

551
00:54:46,867 --> 00:54:48,983
His mouth has sealed up.

552
00:54:51,580 --> 00:54:53,866
Oh, god, William!

553
00:54:53,957 --> 00:54:56,118
William! Get him up!

554
00:54:56,210 --> 00:54:57,620
Hold him!

555
00:54:59,004 --> 00:55:01,871
Children, away from this!
Thomasin, help!

556
00:55:05,344 --> 00:55:07,050
You'll break his jaws.

557
00:55:07,179 --> 00:55:08,464
Father!

558
00:55:09,681 --> 00:55:11,546
What is...?

559
00:55:23,070 --> 00:55:26,608
William... he is witched!

560
00:55:26,698 --> 00:55:28,404
- 'Tis she!
- No!

561
00:55:28,492 --> 00:55:30,733
What horrible fancy is this?
She told me she stole Sam!

562
00:55:30,828 --> 00:55:32,284
Silence!

563
00:55:32,371 --> 00:55:33,723
She gave him to the devil
in the wood!

564
00:55:33,747 --> 00:55:35,237
- They lie!
- What say you?

565
00:55:35,332 --> 00:55:36,947
She turned flora's milk to blood!

566
00:55:37,042 --> 00:55:38,623
She had bade us
keep secret from you!

567
00:55:38,710 --> 00:55:41,747
- It was but a jest to quiet her, I...
- She made bargain with Satan!

568
00:55:41,839 --> 00:55:43,420
She signed his book! Silence!

569
00:55:43,507 --> 00:55:45,919
Don't let her near me!
She'll put a curse on me!

570
00:55:46,009 --> 00:55:48,500
- They conspire against me.
- Thomasin is a witch!

571
00:55:49,721 --> 00:55:52,758
Nay, I'll not hear it.

572
00:55:52,850 --> 00:55:55,637
I'll have proof, or heaven help thee.

573
00:55:55,727 --> 00:55:57,934
On thy knees!

574
00:55:58,021 --> 00:56:00,433
Look me in the eye, daughter.

575
00:56:00,524 --> 00:56:03,812
Dost thou love the word of god?
Yes.

576
00:56:03,902 --> 00:56:06,018
Love you the Bible?
Love you prayer?

577
00:56:06,113 --> 00:56:07,819
Yes. Yes!

578
00:56:11,034 --> 00:56:13,867
We are children of sin all,

579
00:56:13,954 --> 00:56:17,867
yet I tell thee, I have raised up
no witch in this house.

580
00:56:19,626 --> 00:56:24,370
Let us pray,
then we need fear nothing.

581
00:56:24,464 --> 00:56:27,376
We shall never lie open
to the wicked one.

582
00:56:28,844 --> 00:56:30,835
Pray for thy brother.

583
00:56:32,556 --> 00:56:34,075
- You must believe us!
- Evil wretches!

584
00:56:34,099 --> 00:56:35,384
Thomasin!

585
00:56:35,475 --> 00:56:37,466
Pray.

586
00:56:37,561 --> 00:56:43,101
Our father, which art in
heaven, hallowed be thy name...

587
00:56:43,191 --> 00:56:44,772
Jonas, pray.

588
00:56:44,860 --> 00:56:48,728
I... I cannot remember my prayer.

589
00:56:48,822 --> 00:56:51,734
What? Nor I. I cannot.

590
00:56:51,825 --> 00:56:53,440
What nonsense is this?

591
00:56:53,535 --> 00:56:55,651
Speak, children.

592
00:56:55,746 --> 00:56:58,453
Our father, which
art in heaven...

593
00:56:58,540 --> 00:57:00,371
Hallowed be thy name

594
00:57:00,459 --> 00:57:03,371
stop it! Stop it!

595
00:57:03,462 --> 00:57:05,578
Pray, you beasts.

596
00:57:05,672 --> 00:57:07,253
Get on thy knees and pray!

597
00:57:07,341 --> 00:57:10,424
Thomasin!

598
00:57:10,510 --> 00:57:13,968
I don't hear this. This is not so.

599
00:57:19,811 --> 00:57:21,802
It's her!

600
00:57:21,939 --> 00:57:23,770
A cat.

601
00:57:23,857 --> 00:57:25,438
A crow.

602
00:57:25,525 --> 00:57:30,485
A raven. A three-legged dog. A wolf!

603
00:57:30,572 --> 00:57:33,154
She desires of my blood.

604
00:57:33,241 --> 00:57:34,777
She desires of my blood.

605
00:57:34,868 --> 00:57:37,075
- Satan upon me!
- She desires of my blood!

606
00:57:39,957 --> 00:57:43,791
She sends 'em upon me.

607
00:57:43,877 --> 00:57:47,495
My lord, my Jesus! Save me!

608
00:57:47,589 --> 00:57:50,672
- Think on Christ!
- She sends her devils!

609
00:57:50,759 --> 00:57:55,128
I am thine enemy, wallowing
in the blood of my sins!

610
00:57:55,222 --> 00:57:57,304
The lord is my Shepherd,
I shall not want

611
00:57:57,391 --> 00:57:59,507
he maketh me to lie
in green pastures,

612
00:57:59,601 --> 00:58:00,995
and leadeth me by the still water...

613
00:58:01,019 --> 00:58:02,555
I am thine enemy...

614
00:58:05,899 --> 00:58:07,139
I am thine enemy,

615
00:58:07,234 --> 00:58:09,350
wallowing on the blood
and filth of my sin!

616
00:58:09,486 --> 00:58:12,444
- I will fear no evil
- For thou art with me.

617
00:58:15,325 --> 00:58:17,816
Caleb... Caleb...

618
00:58:22,791 --> 00:58:26,033
Cast a light of countenance
upon me.

619
00:58:26,128 --> 00:58:29,495
Spread over me
the lap of thy love.

620
00:58:29,589 --> 00:58:32,706
Wash me in the everflowing
fountains of thy blood.

621
00:58:32,801 --> 00:58:37,340
Holy thine I am,
my sweet lord Jesus.

622
00:58:37,431 --> 00:58:43,552
My lord, my love, kiss me
with the kisses of thy mouth.

623
00:58:44,229 --> 00:58:46,390
How lovely art thou.

624
00:58:46,523 --> 00:58:48,605
Thy embrace!

625
00:58:49,609 --> 00:58:51,975
My lord!

626
00:58:52,070 --> 00:58:54,561
My lord! My love!

627
00:58:54,656 --> 00:58:56,988
My sole salvation!

628
00:58:57,075 --> 00:58:58,906
Take me to thy lap!

629
00:59:27,647 --> 00:59:29,262
Caleb...

630
00:59:31,359 --> 00:59:33,099
Caleb?

631
00:59:34,237 --> 00:59:36,273
Caleb?

632
00:59:36,907 --> 00:59:38,363
Caleb.

633
00:59:38,450 --> 00:59:39,940
Caleb.

634
00:59:40,035 --> 00:59:42,617
Caleb...

635
00:59:43,038 --> 00:59:46,201
Wake up, please! Wake up!

636
00:59:47,876 --> 00:59:50,834
Wake up, wake up.

637
00:59:51,922 --> 00:59:54,664
Wake up.

638
00:59:59,387 --> 01:00:01,753
He is dead!

639
01:00:01,848 --> 01:00:06,182
He is dead!

640
01:00:09,272 --> 01:00:11,604
Jonas, mercy, get up.

641
01:00:13,110 --> 01:00:14,600
Get up!

642
01:00:19,616 --> 01:00:23,029
Get away from him!
Get thee gone!

643
01:00:38,135 --> 01:00:39,375
Thomasin!

644
01:00:39,469 --> 01:00:41,175
Thomasin. Thomasin...

645
01:00:41,263 --> 01:00:42,503
My girl...

646
01:00:56,319 --> 01:00:59,937
This tree will be
lovely come spring.

647
01:01:00,031 --> 01:01:02,363
Do you remember
when we came hither?

648
01:01:04,452 --> 01:01:06,659
Such a pretty tree.

649
01:01:09,499 --> 01:01:12,115
Next year I'll just own us
a wheat field.

650
01:01:13,086 --> 01:01:15,919
Start it at this tree
and end it thither.

651
01:01:16,006 --> 01:01:18,418
We'd have been a proper farm then.

652
01:01:19,467 --> 01:01:24,427
Brought us a big fat milk cow,
finished us the barn.

653
01:01:27,893 --> 01:01:30,305
You must tell me, thomasin.

654
01:01:31,521 --> 01:01:34,729
Tomorrow I cannot keep secret of this.

655
01:01:34,816 --> 01:01:37,398
The council will be called
and thy life is...

656
01:01:37,485 --> 01:01:39,851
- Thy life...
- Will you not believe me?

657
01:01:39,946 --> 01:01:42,858
I saw the serpent in my son.
You stopped their prayer, thom...

658
01:01:42,949 --> 01:01:46,692
- They lie!
- I saw it.

659
01:01:46,786 --> 01:01:49,823
Caleb disappeared with thee.

660
01:01:49,915 --> 01:01:53,407
- I love Caleb.
- And who then found him,

661
01:01:53,501 --> 01:01:55,082
pale as death,

662
01:01:55,170 --> 01:01:58,287
naked as sin and witch'd?

663
01:01:58,381 --> 01:02:00,622
Thomasin, listen to me.

664
01:02:00,717 --> 01:02:02,878
The bargain that was made
is of no effect.

665
01:02:02,969 --> 01:02:05,130
- I made no bargain.
- Thy soul belongeth to Christ.

666
01:02:05,222 --> 01:02:07,884
- I made no bargain.
- The devil hath no interest in thee.

667
01:02:07,974 --> 01:02:11,512
- I am no witch, father.
- What did I but see in my house?

668
01:02:12,520 --> 01:02:14,886
- Will you not hear me?
- Prithee, confess.

669
01:02:14,981 --> 01:02:16,846
Why have you turned against me?

670
01:02:16,942 --> 01:02:20,150
Christ can un-witch us
if you will but speak truth to me.

671
01:02:20,237 --> 01:02:23,855
As I love thee, speak truth.

672
01:02:23,949 --> 01:02:27,817
- You ask me to speak truth?
- I beg thee.

673
01:02:33,917 --> 01:02:37,034
You and mother planned
to rid the farm of me.

674
01:02:38,129 --> 01:02:41,417
Aye, I heard you speak of it.

675
01:02:41,508 --> 01:02:43,499
Is that truth?

676
01:02:45,929 --> 01:02:48,841
You took of mother's cup
and let her rail at me.

677
01:02:48,932 --> 01:02:51,298
You confessed not
till it was too late.

678
01:02:51,393 --> 01:02:53,384
- Is that truth?
- Peace thee.

679
01:02:53,478 --> 01:02:54,763
- I will not.
- I am thy father.

680
01:02:54,854 --> 01:02:57,971
- You are a hypocrite!
- Hold thy tongue, daughter mine.

681
01:02:58,066 --> 01:03:00,853
You took Caleb to the wood and let me
take the blame of that too.

682
01:03:00,944 --> 01:03:02,684
Is that truth?

683
01:03:05,031 --> 01:03:08,023
You let mother be as thy master.

684
01:03:08,118 --> 01:03:10,825
You cannot bring the crops to yield!
You cannot hunt!

685
01:03:10,912 --> 01:03:12,618
- Is that truth enough?
- Enough.

686
01:03:12,706 --> 01:03:14,742
Thou canst do nothing
save cut wood!

687
01:03:14,833 --> 01:03:16,073
Bitch!

688
01:03:16,167 --> 01:03:18,453
And you will not hear me!

689
01:03:20,505 --> 01:03:23,292
Must I hear the devil
wag his tongue in thy mouth?

690
01:03:25,302 --> 01:03:27,133
Ask the twins then!

691
01:03:27,220 --> 01:03:29,006
Go on, ask them!

692
01:03:29,097 --> 01:03:31,509
They spend all day long
babbling to that horned beast.

693
01:03:31,599 --> 01:03:32,839
They know well his voice.

694
01:03:32,934 --> 01:03:34,219
Go to.

695
01:03:34,311 --> 01:03:37,678
The adversary oft comes
in the shape of a he-goat.

696
01:03:37,814 --> 01:03:40,647
And whispers. Aye, whispers!

697
01:03:42,068 --> 01:03:45,481
He is Lucifer. You know it.

698
01:03:45,572 --> 01:03:47,779
- The twins know it too.
- Slander thy brethren no more.

699
01:03:47,866 --> 01:03:51,984
- It is they!
- From my sight!

700
01:03:52,078 --> 01:03:54,140
T'was they and that goat
what bewitched this whole farm.

701
01:03:54,164 --> 01:03:55,404
Lies.

702
01:03:56,583 --> 01:03:59,245
Was't a wolf stole Sam?

703
01:03:59,336 --> 01:04:02,043
I never saw no wolf.

704
01:04:02,130 --> 01:04:03,916
Mercy told me herself
by the stream,

705
01:04:04,007 --> 01:04:06,464
"I be the witch of the wood."

706
01:04:06,551 --> 01:04:08,212
Get up. Rise!

707
01:04:38,958 --> 01:04:41,074
- What is this?
- Speak.

708
01:04:41,169 --> 01:04:43,000
I am no witch.

709
01:04:43,088 --> 01:04:45,107
Get her from me sight!
I'll not have her in this house!

710
01:04:45,131 --> 01:04:46,871
She is no witch, Katherine.

711
01:04:46,966 --> 01:04:49,582
What is the cause, daughter?
Tell thy mother!

712
01:04:49,677 --> 01:04:51,042
I cannot know for certain.

713
01:04:51,137 --> 01:04:52,843
Thou toldst me well thou knew.

714
01:04:52,931 --> 01:04:54,387
I cannot look at her.

715
01:04:54,474 --> 01:04:58,092
Aye, but ye shall.
Thomasin. Thomasin!

716
01:04:58,978 --> 01:05:00,969
Jonas and mercy.

717
01:05:01,064 --> 01:05:03,931
They make covenant with the devil
in the shape of black Phillip.

718
01:05:05,110 --> 01:05:08,398
Dost hear that, ye black minions?

719
01:05:08,488 --> 01:05:12,106
Dost hear that, you devils?

720
01:05:12,534 --> 01:05:15,776
Wake! Wake from this!

721
01:05:16,913 --> 01:05:19,825
Did ye makes some
unholy bond with that goat?

722
01:05:19,916 --> 01:05:22,783
Speak, if this be pretense.

723
01:05:33,054 --> 01:05:37,548
Dissemblers!
Grave pretenders all.

724
01:05:37,642 --> 01:05:39,473
Hear me this:

725
01:05:39,561 --> 01:05:42,553
I will not play a fool
to children's games!

726
01:05:42,647 --> 01:05:44,729
This is no sport, William.

727
01:05:44,816 --> 01:05:48,149
Yet these lies from our babes' mouths
are but trifles to them.

728
01:05:48,236 --> 01:05:51,148
- I do not lie.
- Silence, creature!

729
01:05:51,239 --> 01:05:55,198
Thy son is dead, damned!

730
01:05:55,285 --> 01:05:57,196
- Caleb did but cry Jesus.
- The devil!

731
01:05:57,287 --> 01:05:58,527
Thou know it not.

732
01:05:58,621 --> 01:06:01,237
- The devil will speak scripture too!
- Thou know it not.

733
01:06:01,332 --> 01:06:03,163
Tis not true! We are damned!

734
01:06:03,251 --> 01:06:04,661
Wake!

735
01:06:06,171 --> 01:06:07,957
Fetch the billhook, wife,

736
01:06:08,047 --> 01:06:11,084
and I will smite Jonas as Abraham
would have done his seed.

737
01:06:11,176 --> 01:06:12,416
No, stop it! Stop it!

738
01:06:12,510 --> 01:06:15,502
Fetch the billhook
and I will dash his skull!

739
01:06:16,973 --> 01:06:18,964
- No!
- Do you see?

740
01:06:19,058 --> 01:06:21,674
- Stop it...
- Do you see now?

741
01:06:23,146 --> 01:06:27,515
Please, father.
No, it's not safe. Not with them!

742
01:06:28,067 --> 01:06:30,308
Keep me from this goat.

743
01:06:31,154 --> 01:06:34,317
If that old Billy be the devil,
I'd have danced with him myself.

744
01:06:37,994 --> 01:06:42,829
I'll break thee out upon the dawn
and we'll set back to the plantation.

745
01:06:42,916 --> 01:06:44,827
Think on thy sins.

746
01:07:02,769 --> 01:07:04,851
Are you witches?

747
01:07:07,273 --> 01:07:09,355
Does father think I am?

748
01:07:09,442 --> 01:07:10,807
Are you?

749
01:07:12,862 --> 01:07:14,398
No.

750
01:07:18,284 --> 01:07:20,320
Does he really speak to thee?

751
01:08:48,207 --> 01:08:50,539
It is my fault.

752
01:08:57,258 --> 01:08:59,249
I confess it.

753
01:09:01,262 --> 01:09:03,002
I confess it.

754
01:09:08,811 --> 01:09:11,018
Oh, my god.

755
01:09:11,689 --> 01:09:14,351
My own fault.

756
01:09:15,818 --> 01:09:19,731
I am infected with the filth of pride.

757
01:09:21,532 --> 01:09:23,739
I know it.

758
01:09:23,826 --> 01:09:25,441
I am.

759
01:09:27,038 --> 01:09:30,781
Dispose of me how thou will't...

760
01:09:32,585 --> 01:09:35,372
Yet redeem my children.

761
01:09:37,006 --> 01:09:40,965
They cannot tame their natural evils.

762
01:09:46,683 --> 01:09:51,017
I lie before thee a coward...

763
01:09:52,689 --> 01:09:54,771
And thine enemy.

764
01:09:55,608 --> 01:09:59,692
And I lick the dust of thine earth.

765
01:10:07,995 --> 01:10:10,111
I beg thee.

766
01:10:11,207 --> 01:10:14,290
Save my children.

767
01:10:16,254 --> 01:10:19,621
I beg thee, my Christ,

768
01:10:19,716 --> 01:10:23,425
I have not damned my family.

769
01:11:39,670 --> 01:11:44,505
Me lambs... me angels!

770
01:11:58,981 --> 01:12:02,565
Mother, we have longed to see you so.

771
01:12:03,486 --> 01:12:05,226
As I to thee.

772
01:12:08,199 --> 01:12:12,613
I must wake thy father!
He will be so glad.

773
01:12:12,703 --> 01:12:16,912
No, let him sleep.

774
01:12:39,897 --> 01:12:43,014
We would see you oft, mother.

775
01:12:43,109 --> 01:12:45,976
- Would that please you?
- Aye.

776
01:12:47,029 --> 01:12:50,442
I have brought
a book for you, mother.

777
01:12:50,533 --> 01:12:53,991
- Will you look at it with me?
- Aye.

778
01:12:54,078 --> 01:12:57,320
Oh, one moment now.
Samuel's hungry.

779
01:12:58,749 --> 01:13:01,616
Oh, come, come, little Sam.

780
01:13:02,670 --> 01:13:04,501
Come, come.

781
01:13:16,767 --> 01:13:19,133
Flora? Flora”?

782
01:16:07,021 --> 01:16:08,511
Corruption.

783
01:16:08,606 --> 01:16:10,142
Thou art my father.

784
01:17:14,713 --> 01:17:17,170
What hast thou done?!

785
01:17:18,259 --> 01:17:20,625
- Where are they?
- I know not what I saw.

786
01:17:20,719 --> 01:17:22,710
- Where are they?!
- I did nothing!

787
01:17:22,805 --> 01:17:26,343
She came from the sky! She...
Devil!

788
01:17:26,433 --> 01:17:29,425
You have their blood upon thy hands!

789
01:17:33,357 --> 01:17:35,268
It is you!

790
01:17:35,359 --> 01:17:38,351
- It is you!
- I am your daughter!

791
01:17:38,445 --> 01:17:42,063
The devil is in thee
and have had thee.

792
01:17:42,158 --> 01:17:45,992
You're smeared of his sin.
You reek of evil!

793
01:17:46,078 --> 01:17:48,694
- You've made a covenant with death!
- Mother!

794
01:17:48,789 --> 01:17:52,657
You bewitched thy brother,
proud slut!

795
01:17:52,751 --> 01:17:55,959
Did you not think I saw
thy sluttish looks to him,

796
01:17:56,046 --> 01:17:58,503
bewitching his eye as any whore?

797
01:17:58,591 --> 01:18:00,832
- What say you to me?
- And thy father next!

798
01:18:00,926 --> 01:18:04,009
No.

799
01:18:05,014 --> 01:18:07,596
You took them from me!

800
01:18:09,393 --> 01:18:12,305
- You killed my children!
- No!

801
01:18:12,396 --> 01:18:15,354
You killed thy father!
You witch!

802
01:18:15,441 --> 01:18:17,523
I love you! I love you!

803
01:23:06,190 --> 01:23:11,685
Black Phillip,
I conjure thee to speak to me.

804
01:23:16,492 --> 01:23:19,279
Speak as thou doth speak
to Jonas and mercy.

805
01:23:27,002 --> 01:23:29,618
Dost thou understand
my english tongue?

806
01:23:33,592 --> 01:23:35,628
Answer me.

807
01:23:48,524 --> 01:23:52,312
What dost thou want?

808
01:23:55,906 --> 01:23:57,146
What canst thou give?

809
01:23:59,201 --> 01:24:03,695
Wouldst thou like
the taste of butter?

810
01:24:04,706 --> 01:24:06,867
A pretty dress?

811
01:24:08,043 --> 01:24:12,082
Wouldst thou like
to live deliciously?

812
01:24:13,340 --> 01:24:14,955
Yes.

813
01:24:16,593 --> 01:24:21,257
Wouldst thou like to see the world?

814
01:24:22,516 --> 01:24:24,302
What will you from me?

815
01:24:27,396 --> 01:24:31,184
Dost thou see a book before thee?

816
01:24:40,534 --> 01:24:43,947
Remove thy shift.

817
01:25:06,935 --> 01:25:08,971
I cannot write my name.

818
01:25:10,814 --> 01:25:14,022
I will guide thy hand.

819
01:28:02,277 --> 01:28:05,610
Dd
